# Lead Quanta Platform Architecture

These principles govern all design and implementation. Do not build persona-specific silos or bypass the deal slip / register model.

## Shared platform, persona-specific screens

Do not build a separate system per desk. Use **shared services** with different dashboards, fields, rights, and workflow paths by persona. See **platform-personas** rule for the full persona catalogue, objectives, and required feature sets.

## Deal slip is mandatory

The **deal slip** is the formal transaction workflow object. It captures economics, documents, system checks, approvals, settlement instructions, and audit trail. No investment transaction exists outside a deal slip. See **platform-workflows** for status flow, settlement steps, and register update rules.

## Segregation of duties

| Persona | Responsibility |
|---------|----------------|
| Front Office | Creates deal slips |
| Middle Office, Risk, Compliance | Review |
| Portfolio Manager, Head of Investments, ALCO | Approve |
| Back Office | Raise settlement instruction, confirm settlement |
| Finance | Post accounting |

Do not collapse these roles into a single actor or skip required review/approval steps.

## No settlement confirmation, no active holding

An approved deal is **not** an active investment position until Back Office confirms settlement. Holdings and downstream modules must reflect this gate.

## Investment register is the source of truth

The **investment register** stores the official approved and settled position. It feeds accruals, valuation, maturities, limits, accounting, and reports. Do not treat blotter, pipeline, or deal-slip draft state as the canonical position.

## Every exception must have a workflow

Warnings, breaches, overrides, failed settlements, and missing documents must remain **visible** until assigned, approved, and closed. Do not silently dismiss or auto-clear exceptions.

## Audit trail is not optional

Every create, amend, review, approve, reject, override, settle, post, and delete action must record:

- User
- Timestamp
- Old value and new value (where applicable)
- Reason (where applicable)

See **platform-acceptance** for developer acceptance criteria and MVP build sequence.
